4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: "AN ACT ELIMINATING THE BOARD OF PUBLIC ASSISTANCE;
5 GENERALLY REVISING PROCEDURES FOR APPEALS RELATED TO PUBLIC ASSISTANCE CLAIMS;
6 AMENDING SECTION 53-2-606, MCA; REPEALING SECTION 2-15-2203, MCA; AND PROVIDING
7 EFFECTIVE DATES AND AN APPLICABILITY DATE."
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 Section 1. Section 53-2-606, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "53-2-606. Right of appeal. (1) If an application for assistance for food stamps, cash assistance or
13 nonfinancial assistance, as defined in 53-2-902, or medicaid is not acted upon promptly or if a decision is made
14 by which the applicant or recipient is aggrieved, the applicant or recipient may appeal to the board of public
15 assistancedepartment for a fair hearing by addressing a request for a hearing to the department. The board of
16 public assistancedepartment shall, upon receipt of a request for a hearing, give the applicant or recipient
17 prompt notice and opportunity for a fair hearing.
18 (2) The department may upon its own motion review any decision of a local office of public
19 assistance and may consider any application upon which a decision has not been made within a reasonable
20 time from the filing of the decision. The department may have an additional eligibility determination made and
21 shall determine whether and in what amount assistance is to be granted under the provisions of this title.
22 (3) If the department reviews a decision on its own motion, applicants or recipients affected by the
23 decisions of the department must upon request be given reasonable notice and an opportunity for a fair hearing
24 by the board of public assistance."
25
26 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Repealer. The following section of the Montana Code Annotated is
27 repealed:
28 2-15-2203. Board of public assistance -- allocation -- quasi-judicial.
