2 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Transition. The board of public assistance shall remain operational until
3 all appeals that were filed with the board on or before [the effective date provided in section 5(1)] are resolved
4 by the board. If a vacancy occurs on the board before that time, the vacancy must be filled as provided in 2-15-
5 2203.
6
7 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Saving clause. [This act] does not affect rights and duties that matured,
8 penalties that were incurred, or proceedings that were begun before [the effective date provided in section
9 5(1)].
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Effective dates. (1) Except as provided in subsection (2), [this act] is
12 effective on passage and approval.
13 (2) [Section 2] is effective October 1, 2025.
14
15 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Applicability. [Section 1] applies to appeals filed on or after [the
16 effective date provided in section 5(1)].
